2022
This year has been filled with many many ups and downs, honestly one of the most emotional years I’ve had yet but I’d like to start 2023 with a positive mind set so im making this post as a thank you to the lessons I was able to learn and grow from in 2022…
2022 allowed me to share times with my family and friends that I will hold in my memory forever.
2022 blessed me with a new god baby making a grand total of 7 (which just so happens to be my lucky number). 
To the ladies @pureloungesacramento I couldn’t be prouder of each and everyone of you for all of your growth this year.
To my best friend @janniemathewss I want to thank you for allowing me to learn so many strengths from watching you grow on your journey. 
To my parents thank you for always supporting me and lastly to my husband for following me on the absolute craziness that is my life. You could’ve chosen a much simpler less complicated path but year after year here you are ❤️

Thank you and goodbye to 2022
Hello 2023 ❤️🥂
